'''本地靜止標準'''（'''LSR'''）是[[天文學|天文學]]以[[銀河系|銀河系]]在[[太陽|太陽]]附近物質的平均運動設置的參考座標<ref name= Shu>{{cite book |title=The Physical Universe |author=Frank H Shu |page=261 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=v_6PbAfapSAC&pg=PA261 |isbn=0935702059 |year=1982 |publisher=University Science Books |access-date=2010-04-07 |archive-date=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629060551/http://books.google.com/books?id=v_6PbAfapSAC&pg=PA261 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但這些物質的路徑不是正圓形的<ref name=Binney>{{cite book |title=Galactic Astronomy |author=James Binney, Michael Merrifield |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=arYYRoYjKacC&pg=PA536 |page=536 |year=1998 |isbn=0691025657 |publisher=Princeton University Press |access-date=2010-04-07 |archive-date=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629061257/http://books.google.com/books?id=arYYRoYjKacC&pg=PA536 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。太陽遵循的路徑稱為'''太陽圓''' ([[橢圓#离心率|離心率]] ''e'' < 0.1 )，當從[[銀道座標系|銀河北極]]的方向鳥瞰時是順時針方向，速率大約是220km/s，相對於接近[[銀心|銀河中心]][[人馬座A*|人馬座A*]]的軌道半徑大約是8,000[[秒差距|秒差距]]，相對於本地靜止標準只有微量朝向[[太陽向點|太陽向點]]的運動<ref name=Reid>{{cite book |pages=19-20 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=bP9hZqoIfhMC&pg=PA19 |title=Mapping the Galaxy and Nearby Galaxies |editor=F. Combes, Keiichi Wada |year=2008 |publisher=Springer |isbn=0387727671 |author=Mark Reid ''et al.'' |chapter=Mapping the Milky Way and the Local Group |access-date=2010-04-07 |archive-date=2014-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629060803/http://books.google.com/books?id=bP9hZqoIfhMC&pg=PA19 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=motion>太陽相對於本地靜止標準的[[本動運動|本動運動]]是13.4 km/s。參見，例如，{{cite book |author=Binney, J. & Merrifield, M. |title=op. cit. |isbn=0691025657 |chapter=§10.6}}或{{cite journal |title=On the distance to the Ophiuchus star-forming region |journal=Astron. Nachr. |volume=AN 329 |doi= 10.1002/asna |url=http://arxiv.org/abs/0709.0505v2 |page=12; §2.3 |author=E.E. Mamajek |doi_brokendate=2010-03-16}}</ref>。本地靜止標準的速度在各處是從202–241km/s<ref name=Majewski>{{cite journal |title=Precision Astrometry, Galactic Mergers, Halo Substructure and Local Dark Matter |author=Steven R. Majewski1 |journal=Proceedings of IAU Symposium 248 |url=http://arxiv.org/abs/0801.4927v1 |year=2008}}</ref>。

